  "text": "(See Banerjee et al 2010 for review). In terms of changes at the protein level in schizophrenia, [CITATION_1] found decreases in levels of Nrg1α protein in the prefrontal cortex. [CITATION_2] found no change in Nrg1 or erbB4 protein levels in an aged population, but they demonstrated increased Nrg1-induced erbB4 activation in schizophrenia tissue. In another study, [CITATION_3] found increases in Nrg1 and erbB4 protein in the prefrontal cortex.",
